cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with the synthesis of a random vector with a prescribed joint density, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed encoding algorithm relies on the learned structure of a tree, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also characterizes the achievable rate region for multi-layer latent Gaussian trees, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
